NAME
    hostsctl

DESCRIPTION
    Add or remove entries from '/etc/hosts'

    This function requires at least one parameter with an additional optional parameter
        $1 - name of domain/hostname
        $2 - ip address (optional: default is '$IP')

SYNOPSIS
    hostsctl [option] [host_name] [ip_address]

EXAMPLES
    hostsctl mydomain.local 10.2.3.40 # default is to add entry
    hostsctl --add mydomain.local
    hostsctl --remove mydomain.local

AVAILABLE OPTIONS
    --add       add entry to /etc/hosts
    --remove    remove entry from /etc/hosts